

<h4 style="color:#72A0C1; font-family:verdana; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 200;">Table Cache Checks</h4>
<p style="font-family:Arial; font-size: 13px;">
The table_open_cache controls the number of tables to keep open for all threads. Ideally, the tables_opened status should increase minimally or not at all. Before increasing table_open_cache, be sure enough file descriptors are available in the OS.
</p>
<p style="font-family:Arial; font-size: 13px;">
Table cache hit rate should be more than 50%, however, statements which flush tables might skew these values and cause it to be a high value of Opened_tables. FLUSH TABLES will close all open tables and reopen it which significantly increases Opened_tables value. 
</p>


